ANC Finder was a project to help residents of Washington, DC understand and engage with Advisory Neighborhood Commissions (ANCs). DC is divided into 40 ANCs, each representing about 2,000 residents. The site provided tools to find your ANC and Single Member District, explained what ANCs are and what they do, and offered information about meetings, commissioners, and local governance.
